Lord Year 2020, November 17th, Tuesday

This is my project of a global trashcan for the Workbench I have created by
Blitz2 (Blitz Basic 2.1); it is not completed but, if you are either a Blitz2 or
an AmiBlitz2 programmer (if not search for amiblitz on AMINET), you can complete
it by yourself; the program and its source code is developed in italian (my
native language!) but is partially commented in english.
I am not responsible of any damage can occurs to your system using my program or
its source code.
I have removed a little bug that did give the program the ability to crash the
AMIGA with a great colours number Workbench where it was running always; now the
icons drag and drop window have the TUTTI (ALL), NESSU (NONE) and INVER (TOGGLE)
fully working buttons.
Now are used the best colours not only for the button borders, but also for the
item selection by either the buttons or the mouse; remove an odious bug that did
leave an empty line into the trashing requester; now the Lascia (Leave) button
is fully working.
If a device has not the trashcan the item of this device is not counted. 
Now the items left after a deletion are sorted; a device that has not the
trashcan is no more counted in the deleted files.
Now the vertical slider of the dropped items adapts itselt to the number of the
items left after a virtual to trashcan item movements.
Now the trashcanned volumes management is started!
Correpted some wrong things, the trashcan file management is not yet completed.
Now if the management window is opened and you doubleclick the trashan icon, the
request panel appears correctly without the previous window activation.
Now no more devices are showed, the volumes are showed instead; this is better!
Some improvements made.
Now the program is fully working (attention!) but the Ricic (Recycle) button
is still unused.
Now the manager window should work properly.

